channel.title: "You do not have jdk 5.0. or jdk 6.0."
channel.description:
Hey I'm trying to run my Runescape private server and I'm almost done. The problem I am receiving is that when i try to compiler server using the "perfect compiler" it says "You do not have jdk 5.0. or jdk 6.0." I have download like several different java's, I just don't know what I'm doing wrong. Please help! :mad:
P.s Everytime i click runsever it pops up then disappears very quickly, too fast to read, but it says something java

item.title: "You do not have jdk 5.0. or jdk 6.0."
item.dc:creator: @ZA_H ZÃ©H
item.description:
@ZA_H wrote:

I have never had success with that compiler either.
But I do use a rather good one.

But if there is anything in there like

"C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_06\bin\javac.exe" -cp . *.java

Just change the “jdk1.6.0_06” change the “06” to your JDK update.

Do like so (my update is jdk6u11) "C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_11\bin\javac.exe" -cp . *.java

Then Compile.
If that doesn’t work then try www.google.com and search
for “rs private server compilers”.

Ok, edit your compiler and on the first couple of lines it should say something like this.

See were it says jdk1.6.0_6

Change that to your jdk version.
